  "prompt": "In which and all the cases do e-Commerce companies refund the money?",
  "response": "E-commerce companies typically refund money in the following scenarios:\n\n1. Product-Related Issues:\n- Defective or damaged product\n- Wrong product delivered\n- Product different from description\n- Manufacturing defects\n- Incomplete product\n\n2. Delivery Problems:\n- Product not received\n- Delayed delivery beyond promised timeline\n- Delivery of incorrect/damaged item\n- Delivery to wrong address\n\n3. Quality Concerns:\n- Product quality not as expected\n- Product does not match website description\n- Expired/near-expiry products\n- Substandard product quality\n\n4. Customer Preferences:\n- Return within specified return window (usually 7-30 days)\n- Unwanted/unsuitable product\n- Size/color/fit issues\n- Change of mind (with certain conditions)\n\n5. Payment/Transaction Issues:\n- Duplicate charges\n- Overcharged amount\n- Technical glitches during payment\n- Unauthorized transactions\n\n6. Cancellation Scenarios:\n- Order cancelled before shipping\n- Product out of stock\n- Seller unable to fulfill order\n\n7. Warranty/Guarantee Claims:\n- Product not functioning as promised\n- Manufacturing defects within warranty period\n\nRefund policies vary between different e-commerce platforms, so specific terms and conditions should be checked individually.",
